{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place Parmesan cheese (if using) in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place pistachios, pine nuts, almonds and spices in mixing bowl and toast <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place cauliflower florets in mixing bowl and chop <b>2-3 sec\/\/speed 5<b>. Mix cauliflower with spatula and repeat chopping, if necessary until an evenly chopped consistency is achieved. Transfer chopped cauliflower into Varoma dish and set aside.","Place garlic, spring onions, parsley and coriander in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add mushrooms and wine then mix <b>10 sec\/\/speed 1<b>. Pour mushroom mixture over cauliflower in Varoma.","Place water in mixing bowl, insert simmering basket, then weigh in sweet potatoes.","Place Varoma into position, then steam <b>15-18 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, or until sweet potato is cooked. Remove Varoma, then remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and set vegetables aside to cool and drain for 5 minutes.","Place a large serving bowl on mixing bowl lid, then weigh in currants and baby spinach.","Add dried apricots, reserved spice-nut mixture, cooled cauliflower-mushroom mixture and cooled sweet potatoes to serving bowl. Season to taste, then stir through remaining parsley and coriander leaves with spatula.","Serve immediately topped with reserved Parmesan cheese or cover and place in fridge until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["50 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (optional)","40 g pistachio nuts, unsalted, shelled","40 g pine nuts","40 g flaked almonds","½ tsp ground cinnamon","½ tsp ground cumin","½ tsp ground ginger","½ tsp ground coriander","½ tsp ground turmeric","700 - 750 g cauliflower florets","2 garlic cloves","4 spring onions, trimmed and quartered","8 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","8 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only","200 g mushrooms, sliced","30 g white wine","500 g water","300 g sweet potatoes, cut in pieces","50 g currants","80 g fresh baby spinach, roughly chopped","12 dried apricots, cut into thin strips","½ tsp fine sea salt, to taste","½ tsp ground black pepper, to taste"]}],"id":"r146922","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-ojCSqe-MByM\/XZVQ0bS8yuI\/AAAAAAAAdGI\/foVzM4en6akC_XSqVIWl_qk8n7fYj7cQwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_YX2FiJcwxk-S1Lw2.png","title":"Cauliflower Rice Pilaf with Sweet Potato","publishedAt":"2017-06-26T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"19.3 g","fat":"22.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"27.7 g","calories":"1721 kJ \/ 409 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large serving bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Serve cauliflower rice pilaf as a main course by itself or as a side dish. It makes a great salad to take to your next barbecue or picnic."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","4 portions"]}